  "question": "Eliza's rate per hour for the first 40 hours she works each week is $10. She also receives an overtime pay of 1.2 times her regular hourly rate. If Eliza worked for 45 hours this week, how much are her earnings for this week?",
  "prompt": "Eliza's rate per hour for the first 40 hours she works each week is $10. She also receives an overtime pay of 1.2 times her regular hourly rate. If Eliza worked for 45 hours this week, how much are her earnings for this week?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "460",
  "generated_text": "To find Eliza's total earnings for the week, we need to calculate her earnings for the regular hours and the overtime hours separately, then sum them up.\n\n**Step 1: Calculate earnings for regular hours.**\nEliza works 40 hours at her regular hourly rate of $\\$10$.\n$$ \\text{Regular Earnings} = \\text{Regular Hours} \\times \\text{Regular Rate} $$\n$$ \\text{Regular Earnings} = 40 \\times \\$10 = \\$400 $$\n\n**Step 2: Calculate overtime hours.**\nEliza works a total of 45 hours.\n$$ \\text{Overtime Hours} = \\text{Total Hours} - \\text{Regular Hours} $$\n$$ \\text{Overtime Hours} = 45 - 40 = 5 \\text{ hours} $$\n\n**Step 3: Calculate overtime pay.**\nOvertime pay is 1.2 times the regular hourly rate.\n$$ \\text{Overtime Rate} = 1.2 \\times \\$10 = \\$12 \\text{ per hour} $$\n$$ \\text{Overtime Earnings} = \\text{Overtime Hours} \\times \\text{Overtime Rate} $$\n$$ \\text{Overtime Earnings} = 5 \\times \\$12 = \\$60 $$\n\n**Step 4: Calculate total earnings.**\n$$ \\text{Total Earnings} = \\text{Regular Earnings} + \\text{Overtime Earnings} $$\n$$ \\text{Total Earnings} = \\$400 + \\$60 = \\$460 $$\n\n\\boxed{460}\n",
